"It was shown in Ogilvie & Proctor (2003) that for incom-
pressible fluids there is an exact asymptotic correspondence
between MHD in the limit of large magnetic Reynolds num-
ber and viscoelastic fluids (specifically an Oldroyd-B fluid)
in the limit of large relaxation time. Ogilvie (2002) improved
upon the compressible viscoelastic model of Ogilvie (2000,
